# Routing & Navigation

## URL slugs (Vietnamese)

Public routes use Vietnamese slugs: `/tuong`, `/doi-hinh`, `/cong-cu`, `/tin-tuc`, etc. Do not introduce English slugs for new public pages.

## Two shells

| Shell | Layout | Base path |
|-------|--------|-----------|
| Public | `Layout` | `/` |
| Admin | `AdminLayout` | `/admin` |

## Adding a public route

Update all three together:

1. `Route` in `src/App.tsx` under `<Route path="/" element={<Layout />}>`
2. Entry in `NAV_ITEMS` (`src/config/nav.ts`) with `labelKey`
3. i18n keys in `src/locales/{vi,en}/nav.json`

## Adding an admin route

1. `Route` under `<Route path="/admin" element={<AdminLayout />}>`
2. Item in `ADMIN_NAV` (`src/components/AdminSidebar.tsx`)
3. Title entry in `ADMIN_ROUTE_TITLES` (`src/hooks/useDocumentTitle.ts`)

## Lazy loading (required for new pages)

```tsx
const NewPage = React.lazy(() => import("./pages/NewPage").then(m => ({ default: m.NewPage })))

<React.Suspense fallback={null}>
  <Route path="new-slug" element={<NewPage />} />
</React.Suspense>
```

## Legacy redirects

When renaming trait routes, add redirect components (see `LegacyTraitRedirects.tsx`) — never break old URLs silently.
